## Session 9: CSS-in-JS & Modern Tools

CSS-in-JS libraries colocate styles with components, enabling dynamic styling, automatic scoping, and TypeScript integration. Understanding when they add value vs when they add overhead is a key architectural decision.

### Styled Components

```tsx
import styled, { css, createGlobalStyle } from 'styled-components';

// Basic styled component
const Button = styled.button<{ variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary'; size?: 'sm' | 'lg' }>`
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  transition: background-color 150ms ease;

  /* Dynamic styles based on props */
  ${({ variant = 'primary' }) =>
    variant === 'primary'
      ? css`background: #4f46e5; color: white; &:hover { background: #3730a3; }`
      : css`background: white; border: 1px solid #4f46e5; color: #4f46e5;`
  }

  ${({ size }) =>
    size === 'sm' ? css`font-size: 0.875rem; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;` :
    size === 'lg' ? css`font-size: 1.125rem; padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;` :
    css`font-size: 1rem; padding: 0.5rem 1rem;`
  }
`;

// Extending a component
const DangerButton = styled(Button)`
  background: #ef4444;
  &:hover { background: #dc2626; }
`;

// Theme provider
const theme = {
  colors: { primary: '#4f46e5', danger: '#ef4444' },
  spacing: { sm: '0.5rem', md: '1rem', lg: '2rem' }
};

const ThemedButton = styled.button`
  background: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.primary};
  padding: ${({ theme }) => theme.spacing.md};
`;
```

