### Trade-offs: CSS-in-JS vs CSS Modules vs Utility CSS

| | CSS-in-JS | CSS Modules | Tailwind |
|--|-----------|-------------|----------|
| Runtime | Yes (most) | No | No |
| Dynamic styles | Excellent | Limited (CSS vars) | Limited |
| Bundle size overhead | Yes | No | No (tree shaken) |
| TypeScript | Excellent | Good | Good |
| SSR | Complex (critical CSS) | Simple | Simple |
| Learning curve | Medium | Low | Medium |
| Performance | Lower (runtime) | Highest | High |

### Zero-Runtime Alternatives

Modern alternatives avoid runtime overhead:
- **Linaria**: CSS-in-JS that extracts to static CSS at build time
- **vanilla-extract**: TypeScript-first, zero-runtime CSS-in-JS
- **Panda CSS**: utility-first, static extraction, type-safe

