## Session 10: HTML & CSS Interview Patterns

This session consolidates the most-asked HTML/CSS interview topics, common coding challenges, and the design-to-code workflow.

### CSS Specificity — The Full Picture

```css
/* Specificity: (ID, Class, Type) = (a, b, c) */

div              { }  /* (0, 0, 1) */
.card            { }  /* (0, 1, 0) */
#header          { }  /* (1, 0, 0) */
.card .title     { }  /* (0, 2, 0) */
div.card         { }  /* (0, 1, 1) */
#header .nav a   { }  /* (1, 1, 1) */
style=""          /* inline */ /* (1, 0, 0, 0) — wins over ID */
!important        /* overrides everything (nuclear option) */

/* :not(), :is(), :has() use the specificity of their ARGUMENT */
:is(#id, .class)  { } /* (1, 0, 0) — highest specificity argument wins */
:where(#id, .class) { } /* (0, 0, 0) — zero specificity always */

/* :where() is powerful for base styles you want easily overridable */
:where(h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6) { line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0; }
```

### Classic Coding Questions

```css
/* 1. Center a div both horizontally and vertically */
.center-parent { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }
/* or */
.center-parent { display: grid; place-items: center; }
/* or */
.center-child  { position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); }

/* 2. The clearfix hack (for float-based layouts) */
.clearfix::after { content: ''; display: table; clear: both; }

/* 3. Truncate text with ellipsis */
.truncate {
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  max-width: 200px; /* must have a defined width */
}

/* 4. Multi-line truncation */
.clamp-3 {
  display: -webkit-box;
  -webkit-line-clamp: 3;
  -webkit-box-orient: vertical;
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* 5. Aspect ratio box */
.video-wrapper { aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; }

/* 6. CSS triangle */
.triangle {
  width: 0; height: 0;
  border-left: 10px solid transparent;
  border-right: 10px solid transparent;
  border-bottom: 20px solid #4f46e5; /* pointing up */
}

/* 7. Sticky footer without JS */
body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100vh; }
main { flex: 1; }
```

### CSS Cascade Layers

```css
/* @layer: control cascade order independent of specificity */
@layer base, components, utilities;

@layer base {
  /* lowest priority — easily overridden */
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
}

@layer components {
  /* overrides base */
  .card h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
}

@layer utilities {
  /* highest priority — always wins */
  .text-sm { font-size: 0.875rem; }
}

/* unlayered styles win over all layers */
```

### The ::before/::after Mental Model

```css
/* Pseudo-elements are generated content — always need 'content' property */
.icon-link::before {
  content: '→ ';
}

/* Common: overlay using absolute pseudo-element */
.card {
  position: relative;
}
.card::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0; /* top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; left: 0 */
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, rgba(0,0,0,0.6));
  border-radius: inherit;
}

/* ::before and ::after participate in the box model */
/* display: none hides them; display: block or inline-block makes them sizeable */
```

